Depth Units

column2: Sunny- calm day.  Small green particles in water.
Cloudy day (100% overcast) - small ripples in water- some small green particles.
Foggy- cloudy day. Windy. Medium size waves.
Overcast day- very calm water (like glass) . Did not see green particle.
Lake was unusually high after very high (9 inch) rainfall in the area the previous week
Fairly windy day with filtered sun
Noted a substantial green algae bloom on the west shore of the lake today.
Very windy day with lots of waves- I was paddling a tippy solo canoe and found it difficult to get a good reading but I tried several times at various angles.
relatively calm- sunny day with no sign of algae bloom
light wind- clear day.  Such a big improvement in clarity over earlier readings that I dipped multiple times to make sure.
Very sunny- calm day. Lake seemed unusually clear
Lots of pollen on surface. Recent heavy powerboat activity.
No visible algae. Cloudy day with no wind.
Large patches of milfoil are now visible on the lake. Hazy sun from Canadian fire smoke in the area
Cloudy day. More milfoil visible around the lake.
Clear sunny day. Lake high after substantial rains. Eagle circling above us.
Some algae bloom and polling on surface
Very sunny; not much milfoil showing yet
Partly cloudy; surface algae bloom on west side of lake and milfoil is becoming evident
Less algae bloom than last week but milfoil is evident
sunny day. A little visible algae in spots and many milfoil colonies.
Very windy; somewhat difficult to do reading from the canoe so it might have been a slight underestimate.Lake is very high for this time of year.
Algae bloom. Milfoil has also showed its ugly head.
Milfoil is bad- but the algae bloom has disappeared.
